*** IN CUSTODY ***

9:39 AM Defendant Jose Luis Gonzalez Sr in court.  Attorney Joseph R Kennedy in court for Jose Luis Gonzalez Sr.  DDA William Leroy Brown in court for State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter Natalia Fajardo duly sworn. Interpreter James T. Larson duly sworn. Statement by Attorney Kennedy that defendant does not need interpreter. Defendant informs the Court he does not need an interpreter. Interpreter will remain in the Courtroom to interpret for others in the Courtroom.

Law Enforcement, Detective C. Grunewald, duly sworn & testified, direct exam by DDA Brown; Venue Established; Witness ID'd defn; Cross exam by Attorney Kennedy. State moves for bindover - waives argument, reserves for rebuttal; Defense objects to bindover and moves for dismissal - argument given; Ct binds case over; bail continued

Cash bond is set in the amount of $850,000 (per case). If the defendant posts cash bail, the defendant must report to and comply with Pretrial Services. The defendant shall report to Pretrial Services by 10:00 A.M. on the business day following his/her release from jail. 
_x_ Regardless of when cash bail (if required) is posted, or when a signature bond is signed, the jail shall only release the defendant if the defendant can  be outfitted directly by Pretrial Services with any required equipment prior to the defendant being released from the jail. (PRIOR APPROVAL BY PRETRIAL SERVICES REQUIRED) 
The following checked category(s) are also ordered: _x_ GPS, __ Remote Breath (Alcohol) Monitoring, and/or __ Random Drug Testing. 
NONCOMPLIANCE WILL BE REPORTED BY DCPS TO THE JUDICIARY WHO SHALL RESPOND IN ONE OF THESE WAYS: Schedule bail hearing, Increase Supervision, Issue warrant, No change but monitor. 
- Defendant shall not have any contact, direct or indirect, with any family member of the victim.
- Defendant shall not possess any type of dangerous weapon [as defined by Wis. Stat. 939.22(10)]. 
- Defendant shall not leave Dane County or Jefferson County without prior approval of the Court. 
Parties did not stipulate to waive the time limits for Preliminary Hearing. 
Trial Judge - Br 2
10/17/22-NOTE per Court Reporter-time limits were waived at this hearing.  Language that parties did not stipulate to waive time limits was entered in error.  jla

1:38 PM Defendant Jose Luis Gonzalez Sr in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph R Kennedy in court for Jose Luis Gonzalez Sr.  Prosecuting attorney Thersa Louise Lewandowski in court for the State of Wisconsin. Fayme Filipiak interpreted. Appearance by victims. The defendant was advised regarding their right to an attorney and to the SPD application process if not already represented. Defendant received a copy of the Complaint and waived reading. Court entered Not Guilty pleas as to any misdemeanor counts. Statements by victims. The defendant will need an interpreter for future court appearances.
